page.title: 13MARKET GARDENING
page.content: Since the mid nineteenth century there has been a growing development of market gardening (cultivation of fruit and vegetables in controlled conditions on green houses) these are to the east and west of Keyingham. They were introduced by Dutch families coming to live here, and have developed into large businesses covering many acres. The main crop os tomatoes and produce is speedily transported by road to the nearest city for distribution. They also provide employment for the area although this tends to be seasonal.
